    <note>Gai(1) Jing [19461] His ancestors were Daming, Zongcheng residents and developed expertise in military arts until a lineage member and lineal ancestor of Jing became skilled in medicine (yixue) and moved to Kaifeng to establish his practice. Jing's father was probably the one who moved to Jiaxing. All are unnamed. I am making Jing's ancestral status as physician. His eldest daughter was sickly and became a buddhist nun. Wei Jing, WJ, 17.12b-24a, 24a-27a (wife, born Zhang(2), who died in 1224 at age 85). SHY:ZG, 41.58b. CBD, 4, 3609.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1179:  In office as Huaixi zongling</note>
